```

``` json
{
    "apps": [
        {
            "name"   : "testapp",
            "script" : "public/www.js",
            "watch"  : [ "src" ],
            "ignore_watch" : [ "file_does_not_exist_anywhere" ]
        }
    ]
}
```

_The key `ignore_watch` seems to crash if array is empty; hence the random value._

Okey so now in another console window I open up `pm2 logs`, and load in the app via `pm2 start .pm2.json`. Everything okey so far I the server is live on `3030` and starts all its workers. But if I go to change the version in the `/` route neither do I get a restart of the server in logs, nor does the change reflect if I access `localhost:3030`.

I've confirmed with `pm2 list`, the application `testapp` is identified as `online` and `watching`.
